text: Gösta Horn (24 January 1907 - 10 December 1943) was a Swedish diver. He competed in the men's 10 metre platform event at the 1928 Summer Olympics. He was killed in action during World War II. ==References== Category:1907 births Category:1943 deaths Category:Swedish male divers Category:Olympic divers of Sweden Category:Divers at the 1928 Summer Olympics Category:People from Eskilstuna Category:Military personnel killed in World War II
